As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=January 31, 2008 |title=U.S. Census website }}</ref> of 2000, there were 563 people, 223 households, and 134 families residing in the city.  The [[population density]] was {{convert|614.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2}}.  There were 285 housing units at an average density of {{convert|311.2|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  The racial makeup of the city was 46.36% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 52.40% [[Race (United States Census)|Black]] or [[Race (United States Census)|African American]], 0.36% [[Race (United States Census)|Asian]], and 0.89% from two or more races.  0.71% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.

There were 223 households, out of which 30.0% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 32.7% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 22.4% had a female householder with no husband present, and 39.9% were non-families.  37.2% of all households were made up of individuals, and 20.6% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 2.52 and the average family size was 3.38.

In the city, the population was spread out, with 33.6% under the age of 18, 9.6% from 18 to 24, 23.1% from 25 to 44, 17.9% from 45 to 64, and 15.8% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 31 years. For every 100 females, there were 80.4 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 70.8 males.

As of 2023, the median income for a household in the city was $30,732, and the median income for a family was $31,944.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Bradley_city,_Arkansas?g=160XX00US0508290#income-and-poverty |access-date=2025-09-11 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

